abstract: Democratic presidential hopeful Amy Klobuchar released a plan Thursday to prevent and respond to global outbreaks like the new virus that has sickened people in China and spread to more than a dozen countries, including the U.S.
snippet: Democratic presidential hopeful Amy Klobuchar released a plan Thursday to prevent and respond to global outbreaks like the new virus that has sickened people in China and spread to more than a dozen countries, including the U.S.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Democratic presidential hopeful Amy Klobuchar released a plan Thursday to prevent and respond to global outbreaks like the new virus that has sickened people in China and spread to more than a dozen countries, including the U.S.
headline_main: Klobuchar Proposes Plan to Prevent, Address Global Outbreaks
headline_print_headline: Klobuchar Proposes Plan to Prevent, Address Global Outbreaks

abstract: She asked whether the fact that Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. was presiding over a trial in which Republican senators have thus far refused to allow witnesses eroded the legitimacy of his role.
snippet: She asked whether the fact that Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. was presiding over a trial in which Republican senators have thus far refused to allow witnesses eroded the legitimacy of his role.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren, Democrat of Massachusetts, sent a particularly pointed question for Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. to read aloud in the Senate chamber.
headline_main: Warren puts Roberts on the spot over witnesses in the impeachment trial.
byline_original: By Emily Cochrane and Catie Edmondson

abstract: The first part of Thursday’s session focused largely on the arguments of one of President Trump’s lawyers, Alan M. Dershowitz.
snippet: The first part of Thursday’s session focused largely on the arguments of one of President Trump’s lawyers, Alan M. Dershowitz.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The clock wound down on Thursday as senators posed questions to impeachment trial lawyers in an effort to consider whether to remove President Trump from office.

abstract: President Donald Trump lashed out at his top Democratic presidential rivals Thursday, taking his fight to the first-in-the-nation caucus state of Iowa and the crucial battleground state of Michigan.

lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — President Donald Trump lashed out at his top Democratic presidential rivals Thursday, taking his fight to the first-in-the-nation caucus state of Iowa and the crucial battleground state of Michigan.

abstract: A lawmaker’s push for denser development near transit, overriding local zoning, was thwarted by a diverse group of legislative foes.
snippet: A lawmaker’s push for denser development near transit, overriding local zoning, was thwarted by a diverse group of legislative foes.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — For years, a determined state senator has pushed a singular vision: a bill challenging California’s devotion to both single-family housing and motor vehicles by stripping away limits on housing density near public transit.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg cast himself as the lone candidate who can “turn the page” on the politics of the past while campaigning in Iowa on Thursday, sharpening his criticism of top rivals Joe Biden and Bernie Sanders with just four days until the state's kickoff caucuses.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg cast himself as the lone candidate who can “turn the page” on the politics of the past while campaigning in Iowa on Thursday, sharpening his criticism of top rivals Joe Biden and Bernie Sanders with...
lead_paragraph: DECORAH, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg cast himself as the lone candidate who can “turn the page” on the politics of the past while campaigning in Iowa on Thursday, sharpening his criticism of top rivals Joe Biden and Bernie Sanders with just four days until the state's kickoff caucuses.
headline_main: Buttigieg Sharpens Biden, Sanders Attacks as Caucuses Near
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Sharpens Biden, Sanders Attacks as Caucuses Near

abstract: As Mr. Biden barnstorms the state in the final days before the caucuses, he is chasing more than voters and delegates. The biggest stakes for him might just be cash.
snippet: As Mr. Biden barnstorms the state in the final days before the caucuses, he is chasing more than voters and delegates. The biggest stakes for him might just be cash.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s campaign has quietly rolled back hundreds of thousands of dollars of television ad reservations in New Hampshire and South Carolina in recent weeks and redirected the funds to buy more ads in Iowa instead.

headline_main: How Iowa Could Decide Joe Biden’s Fund-Raising Future
headline_print_headline: Iowa Could Make or Break Biden’s War Chest

abstract: Mr. Biden’s attack on his rival in Iowa came hours after another leading candidate, Pete Buttigieg, criticized both men, in a day of sparring that underscored the pressure they all face to excel in Monday’s caucuses.
snippet: Mr. Biden’s attack on his rival in Iowa came hours after another leading candidate, Pete Buttigieg, criticized both men, in a day of sparring that underscored the pressure they all face to excel in Monday’s caucuses.
lead_paragraph: PELLA, Iowa — In one of his most direct confrontations yet with his top rival in the Iowa caucuses, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Thursday called out Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont for not being a Democrat even as Mr. Sanders makes a competitive run for that party’s presidential nomination, and Mr. Biden also jabbed Mr. Sanders’s record on gun control in among his most detailed remarks on the matter to date.
